<br>
Dear Zeus, King of the Gods,<br>
<br>
Because of my recent punishment, and the harm it shall do to my beloved Hippolyte and her amazons, I shall be in Themiscrya until I feel that the amazons will be able to survive this hard winter on their own.  I leave my crown to you, so that you may think of me while I am gone. Even tho, surely you cannot forget me. I am sure of this. Know that even with this, I still love you, my husband. Despite the pain I feel now. But, know this...I will not forget.<br>
<br>
Hera<br>
<br>
:::As the Queen of the Gods sighed, a cloak appeared about her shoulders....then she dissappeared. At the foot of the now quiet ivory throne, appeared a lone peacock feather in her place::: ~~&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;{{{{@<br>
