<br>
Alecto spoke aloud &quot;Dear Nephew,&quot; she said speaking to Zeus. &quot;You have shamed your crown. Punishing mortals on behalf of Hera has never been your liking. Why begin now? And why begin with the amazons?&quot; She shook her head. Megaera and Tisiphone stood before the throne and in a chant declared. . <br>
<br>
&lt;Megaera&gt; &quot;During the amazons time of harshness, all who cause pain upon them, mortal or not shall have everlasting anguish.&quot; <br>
<br>
Everyone around knew that Tisiphone could do it, and no one would ever challenge the Goddess. Megaera touched the peacock feather. &quot;For you dear Niece.&quot;<br>
<br>
